  "analysis": {
    "summary": "Corbin's foundational essay distinguishing the imaginal (mundus imaginalis) from the imaginary. The mundus imaginalis is a real intermediate order of reality accessed through the active imagination (imaginatio vera), not fantasy. Key source for the concept of the imaginal in Western esotericism.",
    "argument": "There exists an intermediate ontological region between the sensible and the intelligible, the mundus imaginalis (\u0101lam al-mith\u0101l), which is perceived by the imaginative faculty (imaginatio vera) and not by the senses or the intellect alone. This is not fantasy or fiction but a real cognitive faculty with noetic value.",
